settings.title: Christina
settings.quote: A (MUCH NEEDED) SOAK IN THE WOODS
settings.quoteContent:
These bath salts will transport you to the Pacific Northwest. Picture yourself sitting in a clawfoot tub that has been dropped into the middle of Olympic National Forest in WA.

I've lost track of the number of emails I've received that scream "best 10 cabins to book on airbnb" or some similar piece that is urging you to dream up your next woodsy vacation. settings.title: Lindsay K.
settings.quoteContent: Loved this gin and this will be a regular star in my liquor cabinet. I like this with ice and a splash of soda, with maybe a sage leaf or rosemary sprig in there. If I had to create a Gimlet that tasted like California, I'd make it with this gin.

settings.title: Sage of Enlightenment
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz Grapefruit Juice
1 oz Ginger & Sage Agave Syrup*
Soda Water, splash
Ice

Ginger & Sage Agave Syrup:
½ c Water
½ c Agave Syrup
2 1-inch Pieces of Ginger
¼ c Sage Leaves
settings.cocktailRecipe:
Microplane 1 1-inch piece of ginger, add to pot with agave syrup, sage, and water. For the remaining 1 inch of ginger, cut it up and add it into the pot. Bring the mixture to a boil, before simmering for 10 to 15 minutes. Strain mixture into a mason jar, adding the larger ginger chunks in. Let it cool to room temperature before using.

In a glass, add ginger and agave syrup, grapefruit juice and ice. Stir to combine. Top with soda water of choice and mix again.

settings.title: Pumpkin Spice Fizz
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz AMASS Dry Gin
¾ oz Lemon Juice
¾ oz Pumpkin Spice Simple Syrup*
1 Egg White
Pumpkin Spice, for garnish

*Make strong tea with a pumpkin spice tea and use tea in place of water to make 1:1 simple syrup.
settings.cocktailRecipe: Add gin, lemon, simple syrup, and egg white to shake. Dry shake hard, without ice, for 10-15 seconds to emulsify egg white. Then add ice, shake hard for another 10 seconds, and strain into a Collins glass. Add ice, top with soda, and sprinkle pumpkin spice on top of the cocktail.

settings.title: Hibs Don't Lie
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz AMASS Dry Gin
¾ oz Lemon Juice
¾ oz Hibiscus Honey Syrup

Hibiscus Honey Syrup:
1 part Strong Hibiscus Tea
2 parts Honey
settings.cocktailRecipe: To make the hibiscus honey syrup, brew strong hibiscus tea and mix with honey until completely dissolved. Pour the syrup into a shaking tin along with the gin and lemon juice and shake with ice for 10-15 seconds or until the tin is ice cold. Strain into a coupe glass.

settings.title: Bloody Mary
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz AMASS Botanic Vodka
3 oz Tomato Juice
2 tsp Lemon Juice
2 tsp Worcestershire Sauce
2 tsp Olive Brine
1 – 2 tsp Prepared Horseradish, optional
5 dashes of Tabasco, optional
Pinch of celery salt, garlic powder and black pepper

Garnishes: Tabasco, carrot peel, banana pepper, cocktail onion, Castalvetrano olives, and a celery stick dipped in celery salt and Tajin
settings.cocktailRecipe:
Start with a small plate of Tabasco and a small plate with a mix of celery salt and Tajin. Rim half circumference of a highball glass with Tabasco, then salt mixture.

In a mixing glass, stir together tomato juice, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, olive brine, horseradish, Tabasco, celery salt, garlic powder and black pepper. Fill your salt rimmed highball glass with ice, then add AMASS Botanic Vodka. Top it with the Bloody Mary mix, give it one more gentle stir and garnish.

settings.title: Honningbi
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz AMASS Botanic Vodka
¾ oz Lemon Juice
¾ oz Chamomile Honey Syrup
Lemon Wheel, for garnish
Chamomile Flowers, for garnish
settings.cocktailRecipe:
To make the chamomile honey syrup, combine one part honey with one part chamomile tea. In a cocktail shaker, add vodka, lemon juice, and chamomile honey syrup. Fill shaker with ice, cover, and shake vigorously until outside of the shaker is very cold, about 12 seconds.

Strain cocktail through a Hawthorne strainer into a rocks glass with one large ice cube. Top with lemon wheel and chamomile flowers for garnish.

settings.title: Calm Collins
settings.ingredientList:
2 oz AMASS Botanic Vodka
¾ oz Lemon Juice
¾ oz Chamomile Simple Syrup*
Club Soda
Lemon Wheel, for garnish

Chamomile Simple Syrup:
Make strong chamomile tea; combine ½ cup strong chamomile tea and ½ cup white sugar, stir until sugar is dissolved; keep refrigerated when not using.
settings.cocktailRecipe: Shake and serve in a Collins glass with ice; top with club soda.

settings.title: CPH Martini

settings.cocktailRecipe: Pour gin, vermouth, and vegetable juice into a mixing glass/cocktail shaker with ice and stir or shake, depending on your preference. Strain into a chilled martini glass and garnish with a skewer of pickled vegetables.

settings.partnershipText: In partnership with Per Our Last Email.
settings.cocktailRecipe: Muddle kiwi with elderflower liqueur in a cocktail shaker. Add gin, lemonade, egg white, and ice. Shake and strain into a rosemary-smoked coupe glass. Garnish with rosemary.

settings.title: Provence 75
settings.ingredientList:
1½ oz AMASS Dry Gin
¾ oz Lemon Juice
¾ oz Lavender Simple Syrup
2-3 oz Sparkling Wine
Fresh Lavender, for garnish
Lemon, for garnish
settings.partnershipText: In partnership with All Sorts of and Shoppe Amber Interiors.
settings.cocktailRecipe:
1. Juice your lemon
2. Add gin, lemon juice, lavender simple syrup, in your shaker with ice
4. Short shake to integrate ingredients
5. Strain into your chosen glassware
6. Top with sparkling wine
7. Add Ice
8. Garnish with lavender and lemon peel

settings.cocktailHeader: Use AMASS Dry Gin, distilled with 29 botanicals including Grapefruit, Cardamom, and California Bay Leaf for a cocktail with bright, lightly spiced notes.

settings.heading: Is Riverine a gin?
settings.content: While Riverine contains traditional gin botanicals like juniper, coriander, and orris Root, it is not a gin proxy. Rather, it is a nuanced, sophisticated spirit in its own right.

settings.heading: what’s inside the bottle?
settings.content: Riverine is made with the following 14 botanicals: Juniper, Coriander, Orris Root, Angelica Root, Lemon Peel, Cardamom, Sorrel, Cucumbers, Apple, Mint, Parsley, Sumac, Rosemary, and Thyme.

settings.heading: How is riverine made?
settings.content: To create a fully non-alcoholic spirit, we individually distilled each of our botanicals in a proprietary hydrosteam distillation process. In this key step, water vapor, instead of alcohol, is used to extract essential oils for a crisp and evergreen flavor profile that captures the freshness of the Pacific Northwest.

settings.heading: How do you drink riverine?
settings.content:
Sip Riverine simply on the rocks with a splash of tonic, or use it as the base for your non-alcoholic cocktails.

Our recommended serve is:
- 2 oz Riverine
- A splash of your favorite tonic
- Lemon wheel, for garnish

settings.heading: Can i drink riverine while pregnant or driving?
settings.content: Yes! Riverine is an alcohol-free alternative designed to be safe for everyone. If you have any concerns about consuming Riverine, we recommend consulting your doctor.

settings.heading: How long does a bottle keep?
settings.content: Riverine is best enjoyed within three months of opening.

settings.heading: Riverine
settings.content:
At first sip, towering trees sway in the canopy while leafy herbs like sorrel, mint, and thyme grow deep in the damp earth. Mist envelopes the mossy peaks as marbled murrelets swoop in between thickets and streams under soft lemon light, nesting in the treetops when the sun sets west.

On the bed of the forest floor, pines and needles doze off, dotted with raindrops. Feel your taste buds tingle as the crisp cool of terpenes grows sharp in the haze.

settings.heading: WHAT DOES “CASTILE” MEAN?
settings.content: In earlier centuries, an all-vegetable-based soap was made in the Castile region of Spain from local olive oil. By the turn of this century, “Castile” had come to mean any vegetable oil-based soap, as distinct from animal (tallow) fat-based soap. settings.question: ARE YOUR PRODUCTS GLUTEN-FREE?
settings.answer:
GIN - Our Dry Gin is gluten-free and made with a corn base spirit.

VODKA - Our Botanic Vodka is made with a 100% organic wheat base spirit. However, through the distillation process, any proteins are separated from the ethanol so there should be zero gluten, though we recommend consulting your doctor if you have any questions or concerns.

HARD SELTZER - Our Botanic Hard Seltzers are gluten-free and made with fermented organic cane sugar.

NON-ALCOHOLIC SPIRIT - Riverine is gluten-free and made with water and natural botanicals.

HAND SANITIZER - Both our travel-sized spray sanitizers and 16oz sanitizing serums are gluten-free.

HAND SOAP - Our Botanic Soap is gluten-free.

settings.question: How long can I enjoy my AMASS products before they expire?
settings.answer:
NON-ALCOHOLIC SPIRIT - Riverine is shelf-stable and best enjoyed within three months of opening. Refrigeration is not necessary.

HAND SANITIZER - Overtime, hand sanitizer will become less effective but typically, the industry standard for when hand sanitizer expires is 2 to 3 years. This is when the percentage of active ingredients drops below 90 percent of the percentage stated on the label.

settings.question: WHEN CAN I EXPECT MY ORDERS TO SHIP?
settings.answer:
Note: our shipping times have updated for the holiday season as shipping carriers prepare for the busiest time of year! See our updated holiday shipping times

Our typical shipping times are as follows:

PERSONAL CARE ORDERS:

We package and ship out orders within 1-2 business days of your order being placed. All orders are shipped via USPS.

Any orders placed Sunday - Thursday will ship out the next day and will likely arrive 1-2 days later. Any orders placed Friday and Saturday will ship Monday morning.

ALCOHOL ORDERS:

Due to federal regulations, all alcohol orders are fulfilled by our shipping partners. We typically estimate 1-3 business days for fulfillment and 3-12 business days for shipping.

All orders are shipped via FedEx. All alcohol orders require an adult signature upon delivery. If you miss your package, a redelivery will be rescheduled for the next business day up to 2-3 attempts.

*Note: shipping carriers nation-wide are continuing to experience delays due to the ongoing pandemic which has been affecting delivery times on some packages.

settings.question: HOW DO I EDIT/UPDATE MY ORDER?
settings.answer: For any changes to your order, please contact us ASAP so we can update your order before it’s shipped out. If the order has already been fulfilled, there is very little we can do, but reach out and we’ll try our best!

settings.question: HOW DO I TRACK MY ORDER?
settings.answer:
Updates on your order and tracking information will be provided via email. You can also opt into SMS notifications.

You can also visit our Tracking Portal, to track your order at anytime (or in case you don't want to search your email inbox).

settings.question: WHY IS MY ORDER BEING SHIPPED SEPARATELY?
settings.answer: Due to federal regulations, all alcohol orders are fulfilled by our shipping partners, so If you purchase personal care items and alcohol together, your order will come in two separate shipments. You will receive email updates and tracking information for both parts of your order as they are shipped.

settings.question: I MISSED MY ALCOHOL DELIVERY, HOW DO I GET MY ORDER?
settings.answer:
All alcohol orders must be accepted by an adult 21+ and require an adult signature upon delivery. If for any reason you miss your package, a redelivery will be rescheduled for the next business day.

You can also arrange a pickup at a FedEx Office location for free. Simply follow these steps:

1. Enter your tracking link on FedEx.com (you can find your tracking number on your confirmation email).

2. Click the purple "Customize Delivery" button to select the "Hold at Location" option.

3. Enter your order's original shipping address to select the location of your choice.

4. As soon as it's delivered, your tracking link will indicate it’s available for pick up. Visit the location within 5 business days with your I.D. and tracking number.

5. Enjoy!

settings.question: WHAT IS THE RETURN POLICY?
settings.answer: Due to health & safety reasons, we do not accept returns. If for any reason your item arrived damaged or you are unhappy with your online purchase, please contact us and we will make things right for you!

settings.question: WHAT IS ROUTE+ AND WHY IS IT ON MY ORDER?
settings.answer:
Route+ is a premium package protection and tracking solution to give you a seamless delivery experience.

In order to best protect your package, Route+ is automatically added upon checkout for $1 per item. This allows you to file a claim in case anything happens after the package leaves our warehouse (missing packages, damaged items, etc.) This is an optional feature and can be removed from checkout at any time.

If you already checked out and would like to remove Route, contact us and we’ll update your order!

If you have purchased Route+ and need to file a claim, you can do so here.

settings.question: HOW DO I ADD A PRODUCT TO MY SUBSCRIPTION?
settings.answer:
Select the "Subscriptions" tab, then click "Add Product". This will open a window where you can search, view, and select additional products to add to your upcoming deliveries. You may also choose the frequency and first shipment date.

Step-by-step instructions for adding a product to your subscription are also provided here.

settings.question: HOW DO I CANCEL MY SUBSCRIPTION?
settings.answer: Within the "Subscriptions" tab, click on the "Actions" button found next to the subscription you want to cancel and then select "Cancel" from the dropdown menu. On the following page, you will be prompted to enter a cancellation reason.
